VILLAGE_NAME_MEANING: Mboama An Islamic name meaning (Safe Area or town)
HISTORICAL_NAME: It was used as a settlement and later change to Darsalan which becomes a permanent village for habitant. The founder was a farmer called Bash Koroma, he was staying at Gbauguwa village for farming in the village, every day he will cover a distance of about 3miles to cultivate his crops, as a result of the distance he covered everyday he decided to build a hurt and starting passing the night, thus attracted the attention of other habitants due to the fact that the land is fertile and productive. The name was first called Yakima, was was later changed to Darsalan Pa Foday Kaifalla Sesay
COMMENT:
This community is a distance off the PHU and other health facility. The land is fertile for Agricultural practices but lack poor road. The work of the TBA has been stop and therefore pregnant women find it very difficult to access the PHU considering the poor road network.
Malaria, fever, cholera are the common sicknesses affecting children in this community.

The settlement was name Secret Area which was later fine tuned to Gbondoma. Our great parents who found this town are warriors of the Mende tribe
COMMENT:
Distance PHU, poor sanitation, lack of teachers and learning materials in the community school build by community
Malaria, fever and complications among pregnant women more especially in accessing the PHU
